It is indeed amazing how in our days the Pope installs idiots who bave no idea of spiritual teaching, whilst there are numbers of men quite able to take their place. If saith and religion are thus harmed, temporal possession is to blame for it.¹ This too is a sign of Anti· christ, whom it is the first duty of the faithful to withstand. Such leaders of the Church ought to be deprived of their bene· fices. Should laws be promulgated to uphold them, obedience should be denied to such laws. Excommunications therefore are not to be dreaded. At present the Robertians excommuni- cate the party of Urban VI and himself; and the latter does likewise. Both seize upon the property of the Church, wher- ever either is the stronger.
